examples.code:
```
// Basic numeric less than or equal to check.
var x = 5;
var y = 4;
console.log(x <= 5);
console.log(x <= 6);
console.log(x <= y);
```

```
// Basic string less than or equal to check. Case matters for string comparison.
var x = \"apples\";
var y = \"Apples\";
console.log(x <= \"apples\");
console.log(x <= \"bananas\");
console.log(x <= y);
```
